CVE-2026-41407,"OpenClaw before 2026.4.2 contains a timing side channel vulnerability in shared-secret comparison call sites that use early length-mismatch checks instead of fixed-length comparison helpers. Attackers can measure timing differences to leak secret-length information, weakening constant-time handling for shared secrets.",2026-04-28T19:37:44.433,3.7,LOW,NETWORK,HIGH,CWE-208,CWE-208,openclaw/openclaw,False,0.22000000000000003
