CVE-2026-41910,"OpenClaw before 2026.4.8 omits owner-only enforcement for cross-channel allowlist writes in the /allowlist endpoint. An authorized non-owner sender can bypass access controls to perform allowlist modifications against different channels, violating the intended trust model.",2026-04-28T19:37:44.697,4.3,MEDIUM,NETWORK,LOW,CWE-863,CWE-863,openclaw/openclaw,False,0.27999999999999997
