CVE-2026-42420,OpenClaw before 2026.4.8 contains improper input validation in base64 decode paths that allocate memory before enforcing decoded-size limits. Attackers can exploit multiple code paths to cause memory exhaustion or denial of service through crafted base64-encoded input.,2026-04-28T19:37:45.680,4.3,MEDIUM,NETWORK,LOW,CWE-770,CWE-770,openclaw/openclaw,False,0.27999999999999997
