CVE-2018-25307,SysGauge Pro 4.6.12 contains a local buffer overflow vulnerability in the Register function that allows local attackers to overwrite the structured exception handler by supplying a crafted unlock key. Attackers can inject shellcode through the Unlock Key field during registration to execute arbitrary code with application privileges.,2026-04-29T20:16:26.183,8.4,HIGH,LOCAL,LOW,CWE-120,CWE-120,,False,0.25
