CVE-2026-7686,"A vulnerability was found in eyeo Adblock Plus up to 4.36.2 on Chrome. Affected by this vulnerability is the function postMessage of the file premium.preload.js of the component Legacy Premium Activation. Performing a manipulation results in improper access controls. Remote exploitation of the attack is possible. The exploit has been made public and could be used. Upgrading the affected component is recommended. The vendor provides additional details: ""The affected code path is a legacy Premium activation flow that has been deprecated. eyeo has already migrated to a new user account-based licensing system. The exploit does not grant permanent Premium access. The licensing server issues a short-lived trial license (valid for approximately 24 hours) for any submitted userId. On the next license check, the server validates against a real subscription and the trial expires if no valid subscription is found. The researcher's claim of permanently unlocking all Premium features is therefore incorrect. (...) The old flow has been present for years and has not been weaponized at scale to our knowledge. The risk to eyeo and to users is minimal.""",2026-05-03T08:16:01.073,5.3,MEDIUM,NETWORK,LOW,CWE-266,"CWE-266,CWE-284",,False,0.39
CVE-2026-7687,A vulnerability was determined in langflow-ai langflow up to 1.8.4. Affected by this issue is the function CodeParser.parse_callable_details of the file src/lfx/src/lfx/custom/code_parser/code_parser.py of the component Full Builtins Module Handler. Executing a manipulation can lead to command injection. The attack can be executed remotely. The exploit has been publicly disclosed and may be utilized. The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way.,2026-05-03T09:16:03.680,6.3,MEDIUM,NETWORK,LOW,CWE-74,"CWE-74,CWE-77",,False,0.27999999999999997
